  "text": "Likewise, the three clades observed in QLD isolates also demonstrated diversity in their prophage content. Clade B isolates possessed 2 different phage profiles, with some having the same prophage profile as P125109 and some having the same profile as LK5. This difference correlated with the clustering of Clade B isolates with the P125109 lineage or the LK5 lineage in the phylogenetic analysis in S1 Fig. Those in the P125109 lineage contained φSE10, φSE12, φSE12A and φSE14 and φSE20, while those in the LK5 lineage lacked φSE20 but contained the RE-2010 sequence described by Zheng et al., located in the same region as in LK5 [CITATION_1] .",
